@Captain Howdy: On a yacht we say that, right or wrong, the captain is still the captain. But you're right here. Looks like we'll have to consider splitting up the word, or something else to make the word digestible. SAVOY is indeed a different case...

@LooselyKerned: It will be hard to part from the loose kerning, but it's clearly not helping here. Have you seen this one [http://bit.ly/1t7BPQk](http://web.archive.org/web/20150418091016/http:/bit.ly/1t7BPQk) of Quintessentially? Ah... Fascinating you are getting a "yacht-y" impression. I thought that the "1920's NYC" urban feel of Brandon Grotesque would work against me.

Back to the drawing board, thanks to both.
